  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(16) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Paul’s sister’s son.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The passage is note worthy as being the only reference to any of St. Paul’s relations in the Acts. The fact that St. Paul lodged with Mnason, as far as it goes, suggests the probability that neither the sister nor the nephew resided permanently in Jerusalem. We do not even know whether they were members of the Christian society, though this may, perhaps, be inferred from the eagerness of the son to save his uncle from the danger which he know to be imminent. We find that St. Paul had kinsmen at Rome (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 16:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 16:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Was this nephew one of them who had come to Jerusalem to keep the feast, and heard the plot talked of (it is difficult to keep a secret in which forty men are sharers) in the caravanserai where he and other pilgrims lodged? We see, from the fact thus stated, that St. Paul, though in custody, was allowed to hold free communication with his friends. This, perhaps, accounts for the fulness with which the whole history is given. The writer of the Acts had come up with the Apostle, and was not likely to desert his friend if he could possibly gain access to him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Acts 23:16-22",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 23:16-22",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "When Paul’s sister’s son heard, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — How privately soever this business was contrived, the providence of God so ordered it, that, for the deliverance of his faithful servant from this inhuman and bloody conspiracy, it came to the ears of Paul’s nephew; who ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "went and entered into the castle ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Where, as has been before observed, Paul now lay confined; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and told ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "him the whole matter. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then Paul called one of the centurions ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Who commanded part of the cohort under the tribune; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and said, Bring this young man unto the chief captain — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thus we see that Paul, though he had an express promise of it from Christ, did not neglect any proper means of safety. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The chief captain took him by the hand ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In a mild, condescending way; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and went aside privately ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Where none could overhear them speaking; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and asked what ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he had ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to tell ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "him — Lysias seems to have conducted this whole affair with great integrity, humanity, and prudence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "So the chief captain ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Having received the information which the young man had to give; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "let ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "him ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "depart, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "charging ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "him to tell no man ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "what things they were that he had communicated.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
